    "body": "###### Reproduction Steps\r\n\r\n1. `Settings` -> `AnkiDroid - General settings` -> `Language`\r\n2. Select a language whose time unit string on App bar of `Decks` screen is different from the current one. \r\n\r\n   For example, if the current language is `English`, select `\u65e5\u672c\u8a9e`(Japanese) or `Indonesia` etc. \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/162619543-eb32231a-d8de-427d-a6ef-e764e6e81d13.png)\r\n\r\n4. (Then, `Decks` screen gets shown.)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Expected Result\r\n\r\n- All of the strings in the screen have been changed to the ones for the selected language.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/162619731-3ac40b02-0799-439b-9a76-bb6ea0af7aed.png)\r\n###### Actual Result\r\n- All of the strings _except the time unit string on App bar_ have been changed to the ones for the selected language. The time unit string remains the one for the previous language.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/162619931-5de6f472-64c7-4c76-b31f-e286f99c5835.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n- It is not until restarting AnkiDroid, the time unit string gets changed.\r\n\r\n    https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/162621745-21330c7f-ac58-4f6f-8686-53c461365204.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Debug info\r\n```\r\nAnkiDroid Version = 2.16alpha56\r\n\r\nAndroid Version = 9\r\n\r\nManufacturer = OPPO\r\n\r\nModel = CPH1983\r\n\r\nHardware = qcom\r\n\r\nWebview User Agent = Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 9; CPH1983 Build/PKQ1.190519.001; wv) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Chrome/99.0.4844.73 Mobile Safari/537.36\r\n\r\nACRA UUID = 69410480-0b9c-401f-ae8d-94da0f29c9dc\r\n\r\nScheduler = std2\r\n\r\nCrash Reports Enabled = true\r\n\r\n\r\nDatabaseV2 Enabled = true\r\n```\r\n###### Research\r\n*Enter an [x] character to confirm the points below:*\r\n\r\n- [x] I have read the [support page](https://ankidroid.org/docs/help.html) and am reporting a bug or enhancement request specific to AnkiDroid\r\n- [x] I have checked the [manual](https://ankidroid.org/docs/manual.html) and the [FAQ](https://github.com/ankidroid/Anki-Android/wiki/FAQ) and could not find a solution to my issue\r\n- [x] I have searched for similar existing issues here and on the user forum\r\n- [x] (Optional) I have confirmed the issue is not resolved in the latest alpha release ([instructions](https://docs.ankidroid.org/manual.html#betaTesting))\r\n\r\n",
